description:
Add endpoint to get a single tick by ID.

## Endpoint

```
GET /api/projects/:project/ticks/:tickId
```

## Response (200 OK)

```json
{
  "id": "abc",
  "title": "Fix bug",
  "description": "The login button doesn't work",
  "type": "bug",
  "status": "open",
  "priority": 2,
  "owner": "alice",
  "parent": null,
  "labels": ["frontend", "urgent"],
  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "n1",
      "content": "Reproduced on Chrome",
      "author": "bob",
      "created_at": "2026-01-20T10:30:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "created_at": "2026-01-15T09:00:00Z",
  "updated_at": "2026-01-20T10:30:00Z"
}
```

## Response (404 Not Found)

```json
{
  "error": "Tick not found"
}
```

## Implementation

```typescript
// GET /api/projects/:project/ticks/:tickId
const tickMatch = url.pathname.match(/\/ticks\/([^\/]+)\/?$/);
if (tickMatch && request.method === "GET") {
  const tickId = tickMatch[1];
  const tick = this.ticks.get(tickId);

  if (!tick) {
    return Response.json({ error: "Tick not found" }, { status: 404 });
  }

  return Response.json(tick);
}
```

